== 112. RadixSort module
----------------------------------------------------------------

-- Sort an array of u32 (returns rank order, in-place index)
Rank order for the data (indices in ascending order):
  rank[0] = 1  -> value 1 
  rank[1] = 3  -> value 1 
  rank[2] = 6  -> value 2 
  rank[3] = 9  -> value 3 
  rank[4] = 2  -> value 4 
  rank[5] = 0  -> value 5 
  rank[6] = 4  -> value 5 
  rank[7] = 8  -> value 5 
  rank[8] = 10  -> value 5 
  rank[9] = 7  -> value 6 
  rank[10] = 13  -> value 7 
  rank[11] = 11  -> value 8 
  rank[12] = 5  -> value 9 
  rank[13] = 12  -> value 9 
  rank[14] = 14  -> value 9 

-- RadixSort on a small u32 array
  small rank[0] = 4  -> value 1 
  small rank[1] = 2  -> value 5 
  small rank[2] = 0  -> value 10 
  small rank[3] = 3  -> value 15 
  small rank[4] = 1  -> value 20 

