-- Struct assignment copies
s1={1, 2, 3} s2={99, 2, 3} (s1 unchanged after mutating s2)

-- Fixed array assignment copies
a1=[0, 1, 2, 3] a2=[99, 1, 2, 3] (a1 unchanged)

-- Array view does NOT copy - it's a (data, count) pair
v1.count=3 v2.count=1 (mutating one view's count does not affect the other)

-- Resizable array assignment copies the count/data/allocator but not the underlying memory
ra.count=5 rb.count=5 (both views over same data)

